passages.tootipText1:
Average passenger flow: the sum of the real-time cumulative passenger flow of all shopping malls divided by the number of shopping malls
 Peak passenger flow: the maximum peak value of passenger flow among all shopping malls
 Peak customer volume: The maximum value of the peak customer volume among all shopping malls
 Today’s visitor volume: the sum of the visitor volumes of all shopping malls
passages.tootipText2:
Average passenger flow today: cumulative passenger flow divided by operating hours
 Today’s peak passenger flow: the maximum passenger flow from the start of business hours to the current moment
 Today’s peak customer volume: the maximum number of people staying in the shopping mall from the opening hours to the current moment and the time point
 Today’s passenger volume: the difference between the total incoming passenger flow and the total departing passenger flow from the start of business hours to the current moment
passages.tootipText3:
Average passenger flow: the cumulative passenger flow of all shopping malls during the selected time period divided by the number of shopping malls
 Total passenger flow: The sum of the passenger flow of all shopping malls during the selected time period
 Peak passenger flow: the maximum peak value of passenger flow among all shopping malls during the selected time period
 Peak customer volume: the maximum value of the peak customer volume among all shopping malls during the selected time period
 Effective customer flow: the sum of the number of unique customers in all shopping malls during the selected time period
 Sales: The sum of sales of all shopping malls during the selected time period
passages.tootipText4:
The traffic diversion map includes entrance and exit customer flow, store customer flow, radiating store customer flow and departure customer flow, among which:
 Passenger flow introduced at the entrance and exit: converted customer flow directly into the selected store from the entrance and exit
 Store introduction of customer flow: converted customer flow from other stores to the selected store
 Radiating store customer flow: converting customer flow from selected stores to other stores
 Departure customer flow: the customer flow leaving the shopping center directly from the selected store
passages.tootipText5:
1. Trend chart: shows the trend of customer flow conversion at entrances, exits and stores respectively.
 2. Import total passenger flow: the sum of passenger flow from entrances, exits and shops
 3. Number of entrances and exits: The total number of entrances and exits entities
 4. Number of stores: the total number of store entities
passages.tootipText6:
1. Trend chart: shows the trend of customer flow from the selected entity to other stores.
 2. Total radiated customer flow: the sum of the customer flow radiated from the selected store to other stores
 3. Number of radiating stores: the total number of radiating other stores that the selected store radiates
passages.tootipText7:
Total passenger flow: The sum of passenger flow during the selected time period
 Peak passenger flow: the maximum value and time point of passenger flow within the selected time period
 Peak visitor volume: the maximum number of people staying in the shopping center during the selected time period and the time point
 Effective customer flow: the number of unique customers in the shopping mall during the selected time period
 Sales: The sum of shopping mall sales during the selected time period
 Square footage: sales during the selected time period divided by the shopping center area
 Transaction rate: the number of transactions in the shopping mall during the selected time period divided by the number of customers entering the shopping mall
 Price per customer: The sales volume of the shopping mall during the selected time period divided by the number of transactions in the shopping center
